  "text": "The Kafka consumer group rebalance protocol implementation in apache/kafka is composed of 11 Java source files organized across the clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ directory hierarchy. These files define classes and interfaces that implement different roles in the rebalance protocol:\n\nCallback Handlers:\n- StreamsRebalanceListener (interface) in StreamsRebalanceListener.java: Defines callback methods (onTasksRevoked, onTasksAssigned, onAllTasksLost) for handling Streams group rebalance events, specifically for task-based rebalancing in Kafka Streams applications.\n- ConsumerRebalanceListenerInvoker in ConsumerRebalanceListenerInvoker.java: Encapsulates invocation of ConsumerRebalanceListener callback methods (onPartitionsAssigned, onPartitionsRevoked, onPartitionsLost) with logging, metrics recording, and error handling for partition-based consumer group rebalancing.\n- StreamsRebalanceListenerInvoker in StreamsRebalanceListenerInvoker.java: Invokes StreamsRebalanceListener callback methods with error handling and logging for task assignment changes in Streams applications.\n\nRebalance Data and Coordination:\n- StreamsRebalanceData in StreamsRebalanceData.java: Holds protocol-level data needed for Streams group rebalancing, including process ID, endpoint information, subtopologies, client tags, task assignments, and partition-to-host mappings. Contains nested classes (TaskId, Assignment, Subtopology, HostInfo, TopicInfo) that structure rebalance-related information.\n\nCallback Events:\n- ConsumerRebalanceListenerCallbackNeededEvent in events/ConsumerRebalanceListenerCallbackNeededEvent.java: Event signaling that the network I/O thread requests invocation of a ConsumerRebalanceListener callback method on the application thread.\n- ConsumerRebalanceListenerCallbackCompletedEvent in events/ConsumerRebalanceListenerCallbackCompletedEvent.java: Event signifying that the application thread has executed a ConsumerRebalanceListener callback, with optional error information.\n\nMethod Name Enumeration:\n- ConsumerRebalanceListenerMethodName in ConsumerRebalanceListenerMethodName.java: Enumeration providing compile-time assurance for the three callback method names (ON_PARTITIONS_REVOKED, ON_PARTITIONS_ASSIGNED, ON_PARTITIONS_LOST) defined in the ConsumerRebalanceListener interface.\n\nMetrics Management:\n- RebalanceMetricsManager (abstract base class) in metrics/RebalanceMetricsManager.java: Abstract base class defining the interface for rebalance-related metrics recording with methods for tracking rebalance start/end events and failed rebalances.\n- ConsumerRebalanceMetricsManager in metrics/ConsumerRebalanceMetricsManager.java: Concrete implementation extending RebalanceMetricsManager that manages metrics for consumer group rebalancing, tracking rebalance latency (avg, max, total), rebalance frequency (per hour), and failed rebalance events.\n- ShareRebalanceMetricsManager in metrics/ShareRebalanceMetricsManager.java: Concrete implementation extending RebalanceMetricsManager for Share consumer group rebalancing metrics, tracking rebalance total count and rate per hour.\n- RebalanceCallbackMetricsManager in metrics/RebalanceCallbackMetricsManager.java: Manages metrics specific to rebalance listener callback latencies, tracking average and maximum execution time for partition-revoked, partition-assigned, and partition-lost callbacks."
}

